<subSubSection id="C34531CEE838FFCDFF22FDB53D21FC5D" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22FDB53D21FC5D" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22FDB53F3EFDBD" bold="true" box="[199,322,603,629]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body yellowish to yellowish brown (including legs) (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFC7EFDB53A5BFDBD" box="[923,1063,603,629]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 10A–C</figureCitation>
), antenna with scape, pedicel and F1–3 clear yellow (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFE8BFD913FAFFD51" box="[366,467,639,665]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
), then darkened in the following segments; metasoma waxy white in middle of T1 (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFA8AFD913EB5FD75" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
) and ventrally. Fore wing hyaline (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFDB7FD4D3CCAFD75" box="[594,694,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
), with veins pale brown, except veins r, 1–SR, 1–M, apical half of M + CU, 1–CU1 and 2–CU1 are dark brown; pterostigma mostly pale brown, and dark brown apically. Head and mesosoma finely and closely granulate; mesopleuron and metapleuron are smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFB55FD053B6BFCCD" box="[1200,1303,747,773]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
); sternaulus deep and linear ventrally (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFE59FCE13C5FFCE1" box="[444,547,783,809]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
); propodeum nearly smooth, without distinct fields, with a short median carina, extending from base (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFE6BFCDD3F84FC85" box="[398,504,819,845]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
); vein r of fore wing about as long as or slightly longer than vein 3–SR; vein SR1 straight, but slightly concave apically, reaching wing apex; vein r–m present but not tubular (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFB4AFCB93B69FCB9" box="[1199,1301,855,881]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheath dark brown, about 0.3× as long as metasoma (
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFD0CFC953D2CFC5D" box="[745,848,891,917]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
