, length of body (excluding ovipositor): 
<quantity id="4CA7CFA0E838FFCDFC40FC713D86FC71" box="[933,1018,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="4.1">4.1mm</quantity>
.; length of fore wing: 
<quantity id="4CA7CFA0E838FFCDFB0AFC713B3DFC71" box="[1263,1345,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22FC2D3A2AFB81" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22FC2D3F67FC15" box="[199,283,963,989]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Colour.</emphasis>
Body yellowish to yellowish brown (including legs), antenna with scape, pedicel, and F1–3 clear yellow, rest of flagellum (unbroken part) darkened; mandible yellowish, with black tip; palpi whitish; metasoma waxy white ventrally. Fore wing hyaline, with veins pale brown, except veins r, 1–SR, 1-M, apical half of M + CU, 1–CU1 and 2–CU1 are dark brown; pterostigma mostly pale brown, and dark brown apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22FBBD3C4FFAE9" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22FBBD3F78FBA5" box="[199,260,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFEF6FBBD3FE7FBA6" box="[275,411,1107,1134]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 11A, B</figureCitation>
). Finely granulate dorsally; frons medially, just behind antennal bases, slightly swollen and shiny; area between stemmaticum and antennal bases distinctly depressed; inner orbits of eyes slightly emarginate above; eye in dorsal view 2.6× as long as temple; OOL: OD: POL = 35: 29: 17; malar space 1.3× as long as basal width of mandible; scape equal both ventrally and dorsally; pedicel slightly more swollen than F1, slightly shorter than scape; F1 about 5.0× as long as wide, 1.3× as long as F2; F2–4 about equal sized, 3.8× as long as wide; mandible with two subequal, sharp teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22FAC23AD8FA79" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22FAC23F43FA8D" box="[199,319,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFEAAFAC53FA7FA8D" box="[335,475,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 10A–C</figureCitation>
) 2.0× as long as its height. Mesoscutum and mesoscutellum finely granulate; mesoscutum clothed with dense, fine whitish setae, becoming few along lateral and posterior margins of mesoscutellum; notauli very weak to indistinct; propodeum nearly smooth, with a short median longitudinal carina at base not reaching posterior margin; mesopleuron smooth and shiny, with a deep linear sternaulus ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22FA523D64F989" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22FA523F45FA1D" box="[199,313,1468,1493]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fore wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFEACFA553FD1FA1D" box="[329,429,1467,1493]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1293,1317]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,183,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-24@19.[151,1436,181,1269]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, frontal view of head; B, dorsal view of head; C, fore wing. A, B: scale bar (= 0.8×); C: 1.0×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257899/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Vein r arising very near to the middle of pterostigma; SR1 straight, slightly concave near to apex, reaching wing apex; 2–SR+M very short, hardly seen; vein r 0.75× as long as pterostigma width, about slightly longer than vein 3–SR; pterostigma about as long as or slightly longer than vein 1–R1; vein 1–M nearly straight; vein cu–a postfurcal; r: 3–SR: SR1 = 15: 13: 90.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22F9A23CF2F941" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22F9A23E80F9AD" box="[199,252,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Legs</emphasis>
moderately long and slender; metatibia distinctly longer than hind femur, 1.3×; hind basitarsus slightly shorter than following tarsomeres combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22F97A3AC4F8D1" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22F97A3F40F965" box="[199,316,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13647EC0E838FFCDFEAEF97D3FA6F965" box="[331,474,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1856,1880]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,182,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-24@18.[151,1436,181,1833]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. Avga saudita Gadallah &amp; Edmardash, sp. nov. (holotype ♀). A, dorsal habitus; B &amp; C, lateral habitus. A: scale bar (= 1.0×); B, C: 1.1×." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257893" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257893/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Figs 10A–C</figureCitation>
). Pear-shaped, T1 conical, slightly widened posteriorly, about 0.8× as long as its posterior width, finely rugose to nearly smooth; T2 relatively large, with sclerotized inverted U laterally, membranous and skin-like medially, rest of tergites band-like, distinctly wider than long; T3 membranous medially, sclerotized areas of tergites smooth and shiny; ovipositor sheath 0.3× as long as metasoma in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34531CEE838FFCDFF22F8CD3BFEF8F5" box="[199,1410,1827,1853]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22F8CD3BFEF8F5" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" box="[199,1410,1827,1853]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22F8CD3F45F8F5" bold="true" box="[199,313,1827,1853]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</emphasis>
The subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C5F19C6E838FFCDFE00F8CD3C1AF8F5" authorityName=", Al-Sajid, Afrotropical" authorityYear="2022" box="[485,614,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pambolinae">Pambolinae</taxonomicName>
is recorded here for the first time for the fauna of the Arabian Peninsula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34531CEE838FFCDFF22F8A93FDAF84D" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22F8A93FDAF84D" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22F8A93F32F8A9" bold="true" box="[199,334,1863,1889]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C5F19C6E838FFCDFE22F8A93C65F8A9" authorityName="Gadallah &amp; Edmardash" authorityYear="2022" box="[455,537,1863,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Avga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saudita">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFE22F8A93C65F8A9" box="[455,537,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">saudita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from the country locality (
<collectingCountry id="F34822D5E838FFCDFC57F8A93A3AF8AA" box="[946,1094,1863,1890]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
) from which the specimen was collected and described.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34531CEE838FFCDFF22F8613D68F862" box="[199,788,1935,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE06245E838FFCDFF22F8613D68F862" blockId="17.[151,1437,531,1962]" box="[199,788,1935,1962]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B92BBE57E838FFCDFF22F8613F1DF861" bold="true" box="[199,353,1935,1961]" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F34822D5E838FFCDFE82F8613F85F861" box="[359,505,1935,1961]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
(Farasan Islands, 
<collectingRegion id="499BACA7E838FFCDFD20F87E3D74F862" box="[709,776,1936,1962]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Jizan" pageId="17" pageNumber="66">Jazan</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
